The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Giant leap in grants

 A STAFF REPORTER

 The Centre has agreed to increase its grant for Bengal under the Jawaharlal Nehru Urban Renewal Mission from Rs 39 crore to Rs 523 crore.

 Following the announcement, the state government on Thursday decided to seek funds for four key infrastructure projects, including the Dunlop Interchange, Vivekananda Road flyover and the two-tier flyover from the Park Circus intersection to Parama Island.

 The government also decided to seek funds for the Rs 20-crore exit ramp from the AJC Bose Road flyover, Rs 88-crore drainage scheme and Rs 40-crore drinking water project in Howrah, municipal affairs minister Asok Bhattacharya said.

 A detailed project report for the Rs 80-crore Dunlop Interchange project has been sent to the Centre.




